<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
        <h2>About Clock-In Visualization</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="lead">This visualization tool helps analyze and understand block clock-in data from the OylNet blockchain.</p>
        
        <h3 class="mt-4">What is Clock-In Data?</h3>
        <p>
          Clock-in data represents specific events on the blockchain where transactions interact with the clock-in system.
          The visualization shows how these clock-in counts are distributed across blocks, highlighting patterns and maximum values.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="mt-4">Visualization Components</h3>
        <div class="row mt-3">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-3">
              <div class="card-header">Block Chart</div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>The bar chart displays blocks ordered by height from left to right. The height of each bar represents the maximum clock-in count for that block.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-3">
              <div class="card-header">Block Boxes</div>
              <div class="card-body">
                <p>Each block is represented as a box showing its height and maximum clock-in count, with a visual indicator of how it compares to the global maximum.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <h3 class="mt-4">Data Table</h3>
        <p>
          The data table provides detailed information about each transaction, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Block Height - The height of the block containing the transaction</li>
          <li>Transaction ID - The unique identifier for the transaction</li>
          <li>Address - The blockchain address associated with the transaction</li>
          <li>Clock-In Count - The specific clock-in count for this transaction</li>
          <li>Block Max Clock-In - The maximum clock-in count for the block</li>
          <li>Global Max Clock-In - The maximum clock-in count across all blocks</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="mt-4">Technical Details</h3>
        <p>
          This visualization is built using:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Node.js and Express for the backend</li>
          <li>D3.js for interactive data visualization</li>
          <li>Neo4j for blockchain data storage and querying</li>
          <li>Bootstrap for responsive UI design</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
          <h4 class="alert-heading">Note:</h4>
          <p>This visualization tool is part of the larger ProtoStone Processor ecosystem, which provides comprehensive blockchain data analysis capabilities.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
